-- Brazil's Oi gets commitments from 14 banks on share plan, source says
-- By Luciana Bruno
-- Tue Mar 18, 2014 11:26AM EDT
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, March 18 (Reuters) - Brazilian telecommunications company Grupo Oi SA <OIBR3.SA> lined up firm commitments from as many as 14 banks that agreed to buy up to 6 billion reais ($2.5 billion) in an upcoming share offering, a source with direct knowledge of the situation told Reuters on Tuesday.

